PERFORM 4 TIMES
    DISPLAY "PROCESSING"
END-PERFORM.
*>PERFORM executes an action, and you can set how many times it occurs.


PROCEDURE DIVISION.
PERFORM SAY-HELLO 3 TIMES.
STOP RUN.

SAY-HELLO.
    DISPLAY "HELLO".
*>In this instance, you can name a pragraph, either before or after "STOP RUN" (will be seen during compile time), and PERFORM executes that paragraph.


01 WS-COUNTER PIC 9 VALUE 1.
PERFORM UNTIL WS-COUNTER > 3
    DISPLAY WS-COUNTER
    ADD 1 TO WS-COUNTER
END-PERFORM.
*>Condensed and leaving out divisions of program
*>Common errors: failure to increase counter, or setting end condition to a single value that counter skips over (i.e., end at C=3, starts at 2, increase by 2)
*>If this is part of a subprogram that is called without ending, you may want the counter in the LOCAL STORAGE SECTION, as that will reset the counter at each instance.


WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01 WS-COUNT PIC 99.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
    PERFORM VARYING WS-COUNT
        FROM 1
        BY 1
        UNTIL WS-COUNT > 5
        DISPLAY WS-COUNT
    END-PERFORM.
STOP RUN.
*>This avoids needing to specifically set the counter, i.e., "MOVE 1 TO WS-COUNT".
*>Modernly, the period after END-PERFORM may not be necessary.


01 WS-FLOOR PIC 9.
01 WS-ROOM  PIC 9.
PERFORM VARYING WS-FLOOR
    FROM 1
    BY 1
    UNTIL WS-FLOOR > 2
    DISPLAY "FLOOR " WS-FLOOR
    PERFORM VARYING WS-ROOM
        FROM 1
        BY 1
        UNTIL WS-ROOM > 3
        DISPLAY " ROOM " WS-ROOM
    END-PERFORM
END-PERFORM.


FILE SECTION.
FD  CUSTOMER-FILE.
01  CUSTOMER-RECORD.
    05 CUSTOMER-ID     PIC 9(5).
    05 CUSTOMER-BAL    PIC 9(7)V99.

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01 WS-TOTAL PIC 9(7)V99.

OPEN INPUT CUSTOMER-FILE.
READ CUSTOMER-FILE
    AT END MOVE "Y" TO WS-EOF
END-READ.
PERFORM UNTIL WS-EOF = "Y"
    PERFORM PROCESS-RECORD
    READ CUSTOMER-FILE
        AT END MOVE "Y" TO WS-EOF
    END-READ
END-PERFORM.
CLOSE CUSTOMER-FILE.
*>This is an important and common perform procedure involving batch record processing
*>Conceptually: the file is opened, the file contains records, the record contains data; 
*>the priming READ loads the first record from the file, which is then "processed" by whatever PERFORM is;
*>"AT END" acts as an "if no more records exist in this file" trigger, i.e., the end of the file is reached
*>More complete example below.


IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. CUSTOMER-BATCH.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
