        ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  CUSTOMER-FILE.
01  CUSTOMER-RECORD.
    05 CUSTOMER-ID     PIC 9(5).
    05 CUSTOMER-NAME   PIC X(20).
    05 CUSTOMER-BAL    PIC 9(7)V99.

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-END-OF-FILE     PIC X VALUE "N".
01  WS-TOTAL-BALANCE    PIC 9(9)V99 VALUE 0.
01  WS-COUNT           PIC 9(5) VALUE 0.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCESS.
    OPEN INPUT CUSTOMER-FILE
    PERFORM READ-NEXT-RECORD
    PERFORM UNTIL WS-END-OF-FILE = "Y"
        PERFORM PROCESS-RECORD
        PERFORM READ-NEXT-RECORD
    END-PERFORM
    DISPLAY "TOTAL CUSTOMERS: " WS-COUNT
    DISPLAY "TOTAL BALANCE:   " WS-TOTAL-BALANCE
    CLOSE CUSTOMER-FILE
    STOP RUN.
*-----------------------------------------
READ-NEXT-RECORD.
    READ CUSTOMER-FILE
        AT END
            MOVE "Y" TO WS-END-OF-FILE
        NOT AT END
            CONTINUE
    END-READ.
*>It is not required to add "NOT AT END"
*>CONTINUE just means "do nothing"
*-----------------------------------------
PROCESS-RECORD.
    ADD 1 TO WS-COUNT
    ADD CUSTOMER-BAL TO WS-TOTAL-BALANCE
    DISPLAY "PROCESSING CUSTOMER: " CUSTOMER-ID


PERFORM 10 TIMES
    CALL "TAXCALC"
END-PERFORM
*>There is no "CALL 10 TIMES"

PERFORM UNTIL EOF
    CALL "PROCESS-RECORD"
END-PERFORM
*>There is no "CALL UNTIL EOF"

PERFORM VARYING WS-COUNT FROM 1 BY 1
    UNTIL WS-COUNT > 10
